AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYour%20job%20may%20disappear%20altogether%20--%20not%20good%20--%20or%20artificial%20intelligence%20may%20enhance%20your%20job%2C%20so%20you%20actually%20will%20be%20more%20productive%20and%20your%20income%20level%20may%20go%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Georgieva%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUneven%20effects%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IMF%20report%20predicted%20that%2C%20while%20labor%20markets%20in%20emerging%20markets%20and%20developing%20economies%20will%20see%20a%20smaller%20initial%20impact%20from%20AI%2C%20they%20are%20also%20less%20likely%20to%20benefit%20from%20the%20enhanced%20productivity%20that%20will%20arise%20through%20its%20integration%20in%20the%20workplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20must%20focus%20on%20helping%20low%20income%20countries%20in%20particular%20to%20move%20faster%20to%20be%20able%20to%20catch%20the%20opportunities%20that%20artificial%20intelligence%20will%20present%2C%26quot%3B%20Georgieva%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20yes%2C%20a%20little%20scary.%20But%20it%20is%20also%20a%20tremendous%20opportunity%20for%20everyone%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IMF%20is%20due%20to%20publish%20updated%20economic%20forecasts%20later%20this%20month%20which%20will%20show%20the%20global%20economy%20is%20broadly%20on%20track%20to%20meet%20its%20previous%20forecasts%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20%26quot%3Bpoised%20for%20a%20soft%20landing%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Bmonetary%20policy%20is%20doing%20a%20good%20job%2C%20inflation%20is%20going%20down%2C%20but%20the%20job%20is%20not%20quite%20done.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20we%20are%20in%20this%20trickiest%20place%20of%20not%20easing%20too%20fast%20or%20too%20slow%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20global%20economy%20could%20use%20an%20AI-related%20productivity%20boost%2C%20as%20the%20IMF%20predicts%20it%20will%20continue%20growing%20at%20historically%20muted%20levels%20over%20the%20medium%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGod%2C%20how%20much%20we%20need%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Georgieva%20said.%20%26quot%3BUnless%20we%20figure%20out%20a%20way%20to%20unlock%20productivity%2C%20we%20as%20the%20world%20are%20not%20for%20a%20great%20story.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Tough'%20year%20ahead%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGeorgieva%20said%202024%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Ba%20very%20tough%20year%26quot%3B%20for%20fiscal%20policy%20worldwide%2C%20as%20countries%20look%20to%20tackle%20debt%20burdens%20accumulated%20during%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic%2C%20and%20rebuild%20depleted%20buffers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBillions%20of%20people%20are%20also%20due%20to%20go%20to%20the%20polls%20this%20year%2C%20putting%20additional%20pressure%20on%20governments%20to%20either%20raise%20spending%20or%20cut%20taxes%20to%20win%20popular%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAbout%2080%20countries%20are%20going%20to%20have%20elections%2C%20and%20we%20know%20what%20happens%20with%20pressure%20on%20spending%20during%20election%20cycles%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20concern%20at%20the%20IMF%2C%20Georgieva%20said%2C%20is%20that%20governments%20around%20the%20world%20spend%20big%20this%20year%20and%20undermine%20the%20hard-won%20progress%20they%20have%20made%20in%20the%20fight%20against%20high%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20monetary%20policy%20tightens%20and%20fiscal%20policy%20expands%2C%20going%20against%20the%20objective%20of%20bringing%20inflation%20down%2C%20we%20might%20be%20for%20a%20longer%20ride%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E-%20Concentrating%20on%20the%20job%20-%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGeorgieva%2C%20whose%20five-year%20term%20at%20the%20IMF's%20helm%20is%20set%20to%20end%20this%20year%2C%20refused%20to%20be%20drawn%20on%20whether%20she%20intends%20to%20run%20for%20a%20second%20stint%20leading%20the%2