3Cli%3EThey%20detected%20the%20alternative%20signal%20while%20looking%20for%20answers%20about%20the%20universe's%20creation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20discovery%20has%20created%20a%20whole%20new%20cosmic%20conundrum%20for%20the%20astronomists.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENASA%20astronomers%20have%20discovered%20an%20unexpected%20%26quot%3Bsignal%26quot%3B%20coming%20from%20outside%20our%20galaxy%2C%20which%20they%20can't%20explain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scientists%20were%20analyzing%2013%20years%20of%20data%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-fermi-gamma-ray-space-telescope-solar-flares-couldnt-detect-before-2017-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EFermi%20Gamma-ray%20Space%20Telescope%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20they%20noticed%20the%20mysterious%20signal.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20%26quot%3B%3Cspan%3Ean%20unexpected%20and%20as%20yet%20unexplained%20feature%20outside%20of%20our%20galaxy%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20%3C%2Fspan%3EFrancis%20Reddy%20of%20NASA's%20Goddard%20Space%20Flight%20Center.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-james-webb-space-telescope-best-images-2023%26amp%3Bpost-bottom-piano-recommendations%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epowerful%20telescope%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20can%20detect%20gamma%20rays%2C%20which%20are%20huge%20bursts%20of%20energetic%20light%20thousands%20to%20hundreds%20of%20billions%20of%20times%20as%20great%20as%20our%20eyes%20can%20see.%20They%20are%20often%20created%20when%20stars%20explode%20or%20a%20nuclear%20blast%20occurs.%20%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20stumbled%20on%20the%20alternative%20signal%20while%20looking%20for%20something%20else%20entirely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20a%20completely%20serendipitous%20discovery%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Alexander%20Kashlinsky%2C%20a%20cosmologist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Maryland%20and%20NASA's%20Goddard%20Space%20Flight%20Center%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.nasa.gov%2Fmissions%2Ffermi%2Fnasas-fermi-detects-surprise-gamma-ray-feature-beyond-our-galaxy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epresenting%20the%20findings%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20American%20Astronomical%20Society.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20found%20a%20much%20stronger%20signal%2C%20and%20in%20a%20different%20part%20of%20the%20sky%20than%20the%20one%20we%20were%20looking%20for.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22NASA's%20Fermi%20Gamma-ray%20Space%20Telescope%2C%20illustrated%20here%2C%20scans%20the%20entire%20sky%20every%20three%20hours%20as%20it%20orbits%20Earth.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a3bb2c43bb77284b9d0325%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22604%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENASA's%20Fermi%20Gamma-ray%20Space%20Telescope%2C%20illustrated%20here%2C%20scans%20the%20entire%20sky%20every%20three%20hours%20as%20it%20orbits%20Earth.%3Cp%3ENASA's%20Goddard%20Space%20Flight%20Center%2FChris%20Smith%20(USRA%2FGESTAR)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20had%20been%20searching%20for%20one%20of%20the%20oldest%20gamma-ray%20features%20for%20creating%20the%20first%20atoms%20%E2%80%94%20known%20as%20the%20cosmic%20microwave%20background%20or%20CMB.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CMB%20has%20a%20dipole%20structure%2C%20where%20one%20end%20is%20hotter%20and%20busier%20than%20the%20other.%20Astronomers%20generally%20think%20our%20solar%20system's%20motion%20creates%20the%20structure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20the%20researchers%20detected%20a%20signal%20coming%20from%20a%20similar%20direction%20and%20with%20a%20nearly%20identical%20magnitude%20as%20another%20unexplained%20feature%2C%20which%20had%20some%20of%20the%20most%20energetic%20cosmic%20particles%20they%20had%20ever%20detected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20found%20a%20gamma-ray%20dipole%2C%20but%20its%20peak%20is%20located%20in%20the%20southern%20sky%2C%20far%20from%20the%20CMB's%2C%20and%20its%20magnitude%20is%2010%20times%20greater%20than%20what%20we%20would%20expect%20from%20our%20motion%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Chris%20Shrader%2C%20an%20astrophysicist%20at%20Goddard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20week%2C%20a%20paper%20describing%20the%20findings%20has%20been%20published%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fiopscience.iop.org%2Farticle%2F10.3847%2F2041-8213%2Facfedd%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Astrophysical%20Journal%20Letters%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20think%20the%20discovery%20could%20be%20linked%20to%20a%20cosmic%20gamma-ray%20feature%20observed%20by%20the%20Pierre%20Auger%20Observatory%20in%20Argentina%20in%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20astronomers%20believe%20the%20two%20phenomena%20could%20originate%20from%20a%20single%20unidentified%20source%2C%20given%20their%20similar%20structure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20hope%20to%20locate%20the%20mysterious%20source%20or%20develop%20alternative%20explanations%20for%20both%20features.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENASA's%20unexpected%20discovery%20could%20help%20astronomers%20confirm%20or%20challenge%20ideas%20about%20how%20the%20dipole%20structure%20is%20created.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20disagreement%20with%20the%20size%20and%20direction%20of%20the%20CMB%20dipole%20could%20provide%20us%20with%20a%20glimpse%20into%20physical%20processes%20operating%20in%20the%20very%20early%20universe%2C%20potentially%20back%20to%20when%20it%20was%20less%20than%20a%20trillionth%20of%20a%20second%20old%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Fernando%20Atrio-Barandela%2C%20coauthor%20of%20the%20research%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENASA%20did%20not%20immediately%20reply%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-fermi-telescope-discovers-unexpected-signal-coming-outside-our-galaxy-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705262198000%2C%2