nd%20perhaps%20even%20earlier%20for%20others.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMany%20people%20of%20the%20Hindu%20faith%20across%20the%20world%2C%20I%20am%20sure%2C%20are%20overjoyed%2C%20ecstatic%2C%20even%20fulfilled.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%2C%20in%20stark%20contrast%2C%20am%20filled%20with%20anxiety%2C%20pain%2C%20fear%2C%20sadness%2C%20betrayal%2C%20helplessness%2C%20and%20regret.%20The%20external%20clamor%20mirrors%20an%20internal%20disquiet%2C%20a%20constant%2C%20thumping%20noise%20in%20my%20head%20that%20I%20now%20recognise%20as%20my%20heart%20racing%20to%20match%20the%20pace%20of%20my%20anxiety.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20was%2011%20years%20old%20when%20a%20mosque%20from%20the%2016%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20century%20was%20violently%20demolished.%20As%20riots%20ravaged%20the%20city%20of%20Lucknow%20(close%20to%20Ayodhya%20where%20the%20mosque%20was%20located)%2C%20I%20spent%20a%20sleepless%20night%20with%20a%20knife%20under%20my%20pillow%20in%20case%20the%20mobs%20reached%20our%20doorsteps.%20I%20could%20hear%20the%20rioting%20but%20was%20thankfully%20spared%20from%20witnessing%20it.%20I%20woke%20up%20the%20next%20day%20to%20see%20the%20Times%20of%20India%20carrying%20a%20picture%20of%20%3Cem%3Ekar%20sevaks%3C%2Fem%3E%20on%20the%20dome%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20with%20the%20headline%2C%20%E2%80%9CKarsevaks%20Destroyed%20Babri%20Masjid.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20day%20was%20eerily%20silent%20due%20to%20an%20imposed%20curfew%2C%20but%20the%20noise%20in%20my%20head%20persisted.%20I%20recall%20the%20day%20less%20for%20its%20events%20and%20more%20for%20the%20overwhelming%20emotions%20it%20left%20behind%20%E2%80%93%20anxiety%2C%20pain%2C%20fear%2C%20sadness%2C%20betrayal%2C%20helplessness%2C%20and%20regret.%20The%20feelings%20that%20I%20have%20carried%20well%20into%20my%20adult%20life%2C%20that%20have%20complicated%20my%20relationship%20with%20god%2C%20and%20faith%20itself.%20Overnight%2C%20my%20god%2C%20who%20is%20benevolent%2C%20and%20kind%2C%20with%20soft%20lotus%20like%20eyes%2C%20was%20transformed%20into%20an%20angry%20warrior%20king%2C%20an%20unrecognisable%20political%20force.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20temple%20has%20been%20a%20big%20victory%20for%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party.%20They%20stuck%20to%20their%20ideology%20and%20delivered%20on%20a%20promise%20to%20their%20followers.%20After%20decades%20of%20mobilisation%2C%20the%20grand%20opening%20of%20the%20temple%20is%20now%20the%20ultimate%20prize.%20And%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20hurt%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20so%20close%20to%20the%20general%20election%20coming%20up%20in%20less%20than%20six%20months.%20The%20temple%20is%20however%20just%20a%20representation%20of%20the%20complete%20suppression%20of%20anyone%20and%20everyone%20that%20believed%20India%20to%20be%20a%20diverse%2C%20multicultural%20society%20with%20a%20well-functioning%20constitutional%20democracy.%C2%A0%20It%20also%20shows%20that%20not%20only%20is%20the%20BJP%20dominating%20politics%2C%20society%2C%20and%20culture%20but%20also%20controlling%20other%20constitutional%20bodies.%20A%20situation%20I%20could%20not%20have%20foreseen%20when%20I%20was%20studying%20law%20at%20Delhi%20University%20in%20the%20early%202000s.%20A%20feeling%20of%20disillusionment%20with%20politics%20had%20started%20to%20take%20hold%2C%20especially%20after%20the%20Gujarat%20riots%20in%202002%2C%20but%20a%20deep%20faith%20in%20law%20and%20its%20guardian%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%E2%80%93%20had%20existed.%20That%20faith%20was%20shaken%20when%20the%20court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fayodhya-verdict-supreme-court-judgment%5C%22%3Edelivered%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20decision%20in%202019.%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMany%20scholars%20have%20written%20about%20the%20case%20and%20analysed%20the%20various%20facets%20of%20the%20law%20of%20possession%2C%20religious%20worship%2C%20limitation%2C%20and%20inherent%20powers%20of%20Article%20142%20of%20the%20constitution%20of%20India.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20congratulated%20for%20ending%20a%20decades%20long%20problem.%20An%20act%20of%20great%20statesmanship%2C%20the%20only%20possible%20solution%20to%20a%20knotty%20land%20dispute.%20And%20to%20me%20that%E2%80%99s%20where%20the%20problem%20lies.%20To%20reduce%20a%20monumental%20issue%20that%20led%20to%20the%20complete%20breakdown%20of%20law%20and%20launched%20the%20country%20into%20a%20crisis%20of%20faith%20to%20a%20land%20dispute%20is%20an%20extremely%20problematic%20framing.%20The%20court%20itself%20admitted%20that%20it%20was%20called%20on%20to%20determine%20the%20legal%20consequences%20arising%20out%20of%20a%20thousand%20years%20of%20prayer%2C%20contest%2C%20construction%2C%20and%20destruction%20at%20the%20disputed%20site.%20It%20was%20never%20%E2%80%98just%E2%80%99%20a%20dispute%20over%20land%2C%20or%20title%20or%20possession%20but%20one%20about%20doing%20justice%20and%20fairness%20qua%20not%20only%20a%20minority%20community%20but%20also%20people%20like%20me%2C%20who%20believe%20that%20India%20is%20secular%2C%20that%20the%20rights%20of%20minorities%20are%20protected%2C%20that%20might%20is%20not%20right%2C%20and%20Hinduism%20is%20an%20inclusive%20and%20empathetic%20religion.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fayodhya-mathura-varanasi-why-the-coming-week-is-crucial-for-the-hindutva-project%5C%22%3EAyodhya%2C%20Mathura%2C%20Varanasi%3A%20Why%20the%20Coming%20Week%20Is%20Crucial%20for%20the%20Hindutva%20Project%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%20had%20concluded%20that%20the%20Hindus%20established%20a%20clear%20case%20of%20possessory%20title%20ostensibly%20on%20the%20principles%20of%20justice%2C%20equity%20and%20good%20conscience%2C%20but%20the%20decision%20shows%20that%20the%20verdict%20went%20in%20their%20favour%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20belief%2C%20faith%20and%20the%20ostensible%20existence%20of%20continued%20worship%20(longer%20than%20the%20Muslim%20community%E2%80%99s).%20Despite%20whatever%20the%20court%20would%20like%20us%20to%20believe%2C%20when%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20more%20moved%20by%20the%20unshakable%20faith%20of%20the%20Hindu%20community%20undeterred%20in%20the%20face%20of%20an%20Islamic%20Mosque%2C%20that%20Lord%20Ram%20was%20born%20at%20the%20disputed%20site%2C%20rather%20than%20the%20encroachment%20and%20destruction%20of%20a%20Muslim%20religious%20site%2C%20it%20becomes%20challenging%20to%20receive%20the%20court%20as%20guardians%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20minorities%20or%20its%20renowned%20multicultural%20heritage.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJustice%20Kaul%2C%20recently%20in%20the%20decision%20on%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%2C%20recommended%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20as%20a%20trust%20building%20mechanism.%20But%20how%20is%20one%20to%20build%20trust%20when%20the%20building%20blocks%20of%20accountability%2C%20respect%2C%20and%20empathy%20are%20missing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDr.%20Rajeev%20Dhavan%20argued%20that%20the%20Ram%20Janmabhoomi%20case%20centred%20around%20%E2%80%9Cjustice%2C%20equity%2C%20and%20good%20conscience.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20applying%20these%20principles%2C%20claimed%20to%20achieve%20the%20%E2%80%9Cultimate%20balance%20for%20a%20just%20society%E2%80%9D%20by%20ruling%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20prevailing%20party.%20The%20notions%20of%20right%20and%20wrong%20are%20typically%20clear-cut%3B%20even%20a%20five-year-old%20understands%20not%20to%20harm%20a%20neighbour%E2%80%99s%20possessions.%20By%20typing%20up%20the%20issue%20in%20complicated%20legal%20knots%2C%20the%20court%20failed%20us%20by%20ignoring%20the%20interests%20of%20justice.%20The%20Ayodhya%20decision%20was%20unjust%2C%20and%20the%20imminent%20inauguration%20of%20the%20temple%20is%20morally%20objectionable.%20Instead%20of%20embodying%20the%20tenets%20of%20Hinduism%20like%20%3Cem%3Eahimsa%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20peace%2C%20non-violence%2C%20and%20harmony%2C%20the%20Ram%20temple%20stands%20for%20violence%20and%20has%20been%20reduced%20to%20a%20symbol%20of%20a%20majoritarian%20state.%20It%20delivers%20a%20very%20disconcerting%20message%20to%20the%20world-%20you%20can%20get%20what%20want%20by%20ugly%2C%20brutal%20force.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%2011-year-old%20me%20is%20as%20disillusioned%20as%20the%2042-year-old%20me.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDevyani%20Kacker%20is%20a%20lawyer%20working%20in%20the%20human%20rights%20and%20the%20non-profit%20space.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705240178000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F14191654%2FGC1E3sZWUAAAUI-.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fnot-my-temple-a-personal-note-on-god-places-of-worship-and-the-law-governing-these%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Ayodhya%20decision%20was%20unjust%2C%20and%20the%20imminent%20inauguration%20of%20the%20temple%20is%20morally%20objectionable.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fnot-my-temple-a-personal-note-on-god-places-of-worship-and-the-law-governing-these%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Did%20Minissha%20take%20a%20dig%20at%20Radhika%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705239427000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106839098%2Cimgsize-36356.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fwas-minissha-lambas-post-on-being-stuck-in-an-aerobridge-a-dig-