D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F14175134%2FGDy-NU3W8AAJCDG.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMumbai%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Putting%20all%20speculations%20to%20rest%2C%20Milind%20Deora%20finally%20announced%20his%20exit%20from%20the%20Congress%20party%20today%2C%20January%2014.%20Deora%2C%20after%20a%20two-%20generation%20association%20with%20the%20Congress%20quit%20the%20party%20to%20join%20Maharashtra%20chief%20minister%20Eknath%20Shinde-led%20Shiv%20Sena%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20announcement%2C%20made%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%2C%20Deora%20claimed%20that%20he%20was%20concluding%20a%20%E2%80%9Csignificant%20chapter%E2%80%9D%20of%20his%20political%20journey.%20While%20his%20post%20didn%E2%80%99t%20elaborate%20about%20his%20next%20steps%2C%20he%20headed%20to%20Shiv%20Sena%20founding%20leader%20Bal%20Thackeray%E2%80%99s%20memorial.%20By%20noon%2C%20Deora%20had%20visited%20the%20CM%E2%80%99s%20bungalow%20Varsha%20in%20south%20Mumbai%20and%20had%20formally%20joined%20the%20Shinde%20faction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeora%2C%20a%20former%20union%20minister%2C%20said%20that%20with%20his%20exit%20he%20was%20ending%20his%20%E2%80%9Cfamily%E2%80%99s%2055-year%20relationship%20with%20the%20Congress%20party.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Deora%20joined%20the%20Shinde%20faction%20formally%20today%2C%20his%20decision%20to%20quit%20the%20Congress%20party%20was%20long%20in%20the%20making.%20The%20timing%2C%20however%2C%20is%20what%20the%20Congress%20party%20leaders%20have%20criticised.%20%E2%80%9CDeora%E2%80%99s%20exit%20has%20not%20come%20as%20a%20surprise%20to%20both%20the%20Congress%20or%20the%20media.%20But%20just%20look%20at%20the%20day%20he%20chose%20to%20leave%20the%20party.%20Right%20when%20the%20Congress%20began%20the%20Bharat%20Jodo%20Nyay%20Yatra%20from%20Imphal%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20senior%20Congress%20party%20leader%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20leader%20also%20reminded%20of%20the%20September%201%20INDIA%20bloc%20meeting%20in%20Mumbai.%20As%20the%20meeting%20of%20the%20opposition%20in%20Mumbai%20gained%20momentum%2C%20the%20Narendra%20Modi-led%20government%20had%20announced%20a%20committee%20headed%20by%20former%20President%20of%20India%20Ram%20Nath%20Kovind%20to%20explore%20the%20possibility%20of%20%E2%80%98One%20Nation%20One%20Election%E2%80%99%20that%20aims%20for%20holding%20of%20general%20and%20state%20elections%20simultaneously.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20party%E2%80%99s%20communications%20chief%20Jairam%20Ramesh%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20Deora%20was%20worried%20about%20the%20Mumbai%20South%20Lok%20Sabha%20seat%2C%20which%20he%20has%20contested%20the%20last%20four%20elections%20and%20represented%20from%202004%20to%202014%2C%20going%20to%20the%20Shiv%20Sena%20(UBT)%20of%20Uddhav%20Thackeray%20that%20is%20now%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20ally.%20Before%20Deora%2C%20it%20was%20his%20father%2C%20Murli%20Deora%2C%20a%20staunch%20Congress%20loyalist%2C%20who%20was%20elected%20from%20the%20constituency%20for%20at%20least%20four%20terms.%20But%20Milind%20Deora%20lost%20the%20seat%20both%20in%20the%202014%20and%202019%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Mumbai%20South%20seat%20became%20a%20bone%20of%20contention%20after%20the%20Uddhav%20Thackeray%20led%20Sena%20(UBT)%20wanted%20to%20lay%20claims%20on%20the%20seat%20as%20MP%20Arvind%20Sawant%2C%20one%20of%20the%20few%20Thackeray%20loyalists%2C%20has%20a%20good%20clout%20in%20the%20constituency.%20Deora%20lost%20both%202014%20and%202019%20elections%20against%20Sawant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20with%20Deora%E2%80%99s%20exit%2C%20the%20seat%20might%20after%20all%20remain%20with%20the%20Thackeray%20faction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERamesh%20told%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fpolitical-pulse%2Fwhy-milind-deora-quit-congress-joined-shiv-sena-9108771%2F%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fpolitical-pulse%2Fwhy-milind-deora-quit-congress-joined-shiv-sena-9108771%2F%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1705318538871000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1OVSSLiOvh9a8VBeAygBc2%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3EIndian%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EExpress%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20Deora%20wanted%20him%20to%20intervene%20and%20put%20in%20a%20word%20with%20Rahul%20Gandhi.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20spoke%20to%20me%20on%20Friday.%20He%20wanted%20me%20to%20explain%20to%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20that%20his%20seat%20was%20going.%20He%20said%20he%20is%20concerned.%20He%20messaged%20me%20at%202.48%20pm.%20I%20spoke%20to%20him%20at%203.40%20pm.%20I%20told%20him%20to%20meet%20Rahul%20and%20explain%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ramesh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20South%20Mumbai%20constituency%2C%20considered%20a%20posh%20part%20of%20the%20city%2C%20comprises%20both%20skyscrapers%20and%20sprawling%20slums.%20The%20constituency%20has%20for%20long%20remained%20loyal%20to%20the%20Congress%20party.%20But%20it%20changed%20in%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20Deora%E2%80%99s%20exit%2C%20Thackery%20faction%E2%80%99s%20leader%20and%20Saamna%20newspapers%20editor%20Sanjay%20Raut%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CSawant%20is%20a%20two-time%20MP.%20What%20is%20wrong%20with%20him%20contesting%20once%20again%3F%E2%80%9D%20He%20further%20added%20that%20his%20party%20won%E2%80%99t%20make%20any%20compromise%20on%20this%20front.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202012%2C%20when%20Milind%20Deora%20entered%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20he%20was%2029-year-old.%20He%20was%20one%20of%20the%20youngest%20MPs%20and%20considered%20to%20be%20very%20close%20to%20Rahul%20Gandhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeora%20had%20blamed%20the%20%E2%80%9CModi%20wave%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%202014%20election%20for%20losing%20an%20otherwise%20safe%20congress%20seat.%20However%2C%20in%202019%2C%20despite%20concerted%20efforts%20from%20the%20party%20and%20even%20an%20endorsement%20from%20Mukesh%20Ambani%20%E2%80%93%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20industrialists%20in%20the%20country%20%E2%80%93%20he%20could%20not%20salvage%20the%20seat.%20He%20was%20the%20Mumbai%20chief%20of%20the%20party%20at%20the%20time%20and%20had%20quit%20abruptly%20from%20his%20post%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20campaign%20to%20focus%20on%20his%20personal%20efforts%20to%20win%20back%20the%20seat.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705235293000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F14175134%2FGDy-NU3W8AAJCDG.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fend-of-a-significant-chapter-as-milind-deora-joins-shiv-senas-shinde-faction%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'Deora%E2%80%99s%20exit%20has%20not%20come%20as%20a%20surprise%20to%20both%20the%20Congress%20or%20the%20media.%20But%20just%20look%20at%20the%20day%20he%20chose%20to%20leave%20the%20party.'%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fend-of-a-significant-chapter-as-milind-deora-joins-shiv-senas-shinde-faction%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'This%20Is%20a%20Poem%20that%20Shouldn%E2%80%99t%20Be%20Written...'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F14163751%2FCopy-of-Copy-of-Lead-image-size-7.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20following%20is%20an%20excerpt%20from%20poet%20K.%20Srilata%E2%80%99s%20book%20%3Cem%3EThree%20Women%20in%20a%20Single-Room%20House%3C%2Fem%3E%20published%20by%20Sahitya%20Akademi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20328px)%2085vw%2C%20328px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F14162842%2FScreenshot-2024-01-14-at-4.28.21-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22328%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F14162842%2FScreenshot-2024-01-14-at-4.28.21-PM.png%20722w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content